str(dat$appIncome)

dat$appIncome<-as.numeric(dat$appIncome)  #converting appincome to numerical variable

6

Binning adjustment(in progress)

breaks_adj =list(
  appAge=c("24", "27", "33", "41"), 
  appChkSv=c("None", "Savings", "Checking", "Chk & Sv"), 
  appFinanceCo=c("Unsecured", "Unknown%,%Retail", "National", "Home Equity"), 
  appOcc=c("u%,%s%,%k", "g%,%w", "f", "y%,%b", "h%,%p%,%o%,%r%,%e"), 
  appResidence=c("Parents", "Renting%,%Unknown%,%Sublease", "Owns Home"), 
  #appOrigScore=c("180", "190", "200", "214", "226"), 
  appTimeAddress=c("2", "4", "6", "10", "17", "24"), 
  cbFICO=c("550", "600", "625", "650", "675", "700", "725", "750"), 
  cbInq5Mos=c("1", "2", "3", "10"), 
  cbMosAvg=c("5", "10", "15", "19"), 
  cbMosDlq=c("5", "16", "22", "26"), 
  cbMosInq=c("1", "2"), 
  cbTimeFileYears=c("3", "5", "10", "15"), 
  cbUtilizn=c("36", "45", "100")
) 

bins_adj = woebin(dt_f, y="target", breaks_list=breaks_adj)
## [INFO] creating woe binning ...

7

Converting train and test into woe values

dt_woe_list = lapply(dt_list, function(x) woebin_ply(x, bins_adj))
## [INFO] converting into woe values ... 
## [INFO] converting into woe values ...

8

glm / selecting variables

m1 = glm( target ~ ., family = binomial(), data = dt_woe_list$train)
m_step = step(m1, direction="both", trace = FALSE)
m2 = eval(m_step$call)
vif(m2, merge_coef = TRUE)
